quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  25,45,"Did you not see how you Master makes the shadow longer, and if He wanted He would have made it stand still, and We made the sun its guide"
  25,46,"Then We pull it toward Ourselves, an easy pull"
  25,47,"And He is the One who made the night as a cover for you, and the sleep as a rest, and He made the day to rise up (and work)"
  25,48,"And He is the One who sent the winds as good news before His mercy, and We sent down pure water from the sky"
  25,49,"In order to bring the dead land back to life with it, and make Our numerous creation of livestock and human beings drink it"
  25,50,"And We have certainly explained it to them (in various ways) so that they may take notice, but most people refuse to be anything except ungrateful (and disbeliever)"
  25,51,"And if We wanted, We would have raised a warner in every town"
  25,52,"So do not obey the disbelievers, and try hard against them with it (Quran), a great try"
  25,53,"And He is the One who merged the two seas, this one sweet and drinkable and that one salty and bitter, and He placed a barrier and a forbidden ban between them"
  25,54,"And He is the One who created a human being from the water, then He made him blood relative and marriage relative. Your Master is capable"
  25,55,"And they serve other than God that which does not benefit them and does not harm them, and the disbeliever is a supporter (of others) against his Master"
  25,56,We only sent you as a giver of good news and a warner
  25,57,"Say: I do not ask you for any wage for it, except that someone wants to take a path to his Master"
  25,58,"And put your trust in the One who lives and does not die, and glorify Him with His praise, and He is enough to be well informed about His servants' sins"
  25,59,"The One who created the skies and the earth and whatever between them in six stages, then He settled on the throne, the beneficent. So ask about Him from a well informed one"
  25,60,"And when it is said to them be humble before the beneficent, they say: who is the beneficent, should we prostrate (and be humble) to what you order us? And it increases their disgust (and hatred)"